<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2742] SourceTaskOffsetCommitter does not properly remove commit tasks when they are already in progress</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2742</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The current implementation is relying on ScheduledExecutorService to cancel the task, but this doesn&apos;t handle in-progress tasks and can result in stopping source tasks not completing a final offset commit before considering the task fully stopped. This can allow rebalancing to proceed before offsets are fully committed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
